<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go out with the tide • go with the tide</xh5><p> <i>go out with the tide</i>—(of hopes, popularity, etc.) diminish; decline: Hereford’s hopes <u>went out with the tide</u> ... washed away after only three minutes when Lightbourne made it onenil.</p><p> <i>go with the tide</i>—(also: drift with the tide) act or think as the majority of people do: You’re pretty good at adapting to change. In fact, you’d rather go with the tide than against it.</p> </entry>
